# .gitignore Quick Reference
#
# Syntax rules:
#   • Lines starting with '#' are comments.
#   • Blank lines are ignored.
#   • Patterns are evaluated top-to-bottom; the last matching rule wins.
#
# Pattern basics:
#   • No leading '/'  = match anywhere in the repo.
#   • Leading '/'     = match only from the repo root.
#   • Trailing '/'    = match only directories, not files.
#   • '*'  = match zero or more characters in a single path segment.
#   • '**' = match across directory levels.
#   • '!'  = negate (unignore) a match from a previous rule.
#
# Common pattern meanings:
#   Pattern       Matches
#   -------       ----------------------------------------------------------
#   build         Any file OR directory named "build" at any depth.
#   build/        Any directory named "build" at any depth.
#   /build/       Directory named "build" at repo root only.
#   *.log         Any file ending in .log at any depth.
#   src/**/temp/  "temp" directories anywhere under a "src" folder.
#
# Edge case – directory vs file with same name:
#   • To ignore the directory but keep a file with the same name:
#       build/         # ignore directories named "build"
#       !build         # keep a file literally named "build"
#
# Negation example:
#   build/              # ignore all build directories
#   !src/main/resources/build/   # but keep this specific one
#

